The paper proposes ontology-based extensions of the Vector Space Model for text retrieval, which is a common technique used in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). This suggests that the paper belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of named entities, which are often studied in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of documents and queries, which is a topic studied in the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve search quality, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
